Find Krita’s Snap desktop entry:
ls /var/lib/snapd/desktop/applications/krita*

You’ll see something like:
/var/lib/snapd/desktop/applications/krita_krita.desktop


Open it for editing:
sudo nano /var/lib/snapd/desktop/applications/krita_krita.desktop


Look for the line starting with:
Icon=/snap/krita/current/meta/gui/krita.png

Then update the desktop database:
sudo update-desktop-database


Log out and log back in.

